ions\/shallots, trimmed and cut into pieces","500 g pork mince","½ tsp ground white pepper","1 tsp white sugar","¼ tsp Chinese five spice powder (see Tips)","1 tbsp oyster sauce","2 tbsp soy sauce","2 tbsp sesame oil","1 tbsp Chinese cooking wine"]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["oil, for greasing","plain flour, for dusting","700 g water"]}],"id":"r313515","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-jnYYEsmTuyA\/XZaqcDgvLOI\/AAAAAAAAhck\/k-_RH_xc-u0GlwRcro4bOt4Mu9g9WI33gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ZPz6HZ0EhWiWRzWf.png","title":"Steamed pork buns (baozi)","publishedAt":"2018-07-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{},"usefulItems":"plastic wrap, rolling pin, bowl, thermal serving bowl or other large bowl, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["To make your own Chinese five-spice powder, please refer to the recipe in the \"Hong Kong-style roast pork belly\" recipe in this collection.","You can serve these buns on their own, or with any dipping sauce of choice, such as soy sauce."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","2h 30m","24 portions"]}